<parameter name="content"># Fix Plan - Relative Paths for HTML Files

## Problem
HTML files use absolute paths (`/css/styles.css`) which only work when served via Express server.

## Solution
Change to relative paths so the site works both ways.

## Files to Update
- [ ] public/index.html - Change absolute paths to relative
- [ ] public/about.html - Change absolute paths to relative
- [ ] public/services.html - Change absolute paths to relative
- [ ] public/contact.html - Change absolute paths to relative

## Path Changes Needed
| From | To |
|------|-----|
| href="/css/styles.css" | href="css/styles.css" |
| src="/js/main.js" | src="js/main.js" |
| src="/images/logo.svg" | src="images/logo.svg" |
| href="/images/logo.svg" | href="images/logo.svg" |

## Verification Steps
- [ ] Check CSS syntax with node -c
- [ ] Check JS syntax with node -c
- [ ] Test server and verify files load correctly
</parameter>
